Object Oriented Design Process
Created by Sam Li
Date: 11/17/2025

Analysis:
    Domain:

        1. Diamond
        2. Girl
        3. Driver that runs the program

    Function Points:

        1. Diamond:
            i. takes carats and values
        2. Girl:
            i. takes name, and a diamond object
        3. Driver:
            i. loops in new values and output the new values

    Scenarios:

        1. Example:
            i.  Girl has no diamond
            ii. Girl receives a diamond, and accepts it
            iii.Girl receives new diamond, new diamond is larger, and she accepts it
            iv. Girl receives a third diamond, third diamond is smaller, and she rejects it

Design:

    Class and Objects:

        1. Class Girl: myGirl
        2. Class Diamond: myDiamond

    Data:

        1. Girl: String name, diamond
        2. Diamond: int carat, int value

    Methods:

        1. Diamond:
            i. constructor
            ii. setter and getter
            iii. toString

        2. Girl:
            i. constructor
            ii. setter and getter
            iii. toString